<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Puerto Escondido</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.327000,25.819000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ligüí</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.266000,25.740000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Notrí</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.244000,25.700000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Agua Verde turn (spur)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.070000,25.500000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ciudad Insurgentes</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.770700,25.256600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ciudad Constitución</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.662800,25.031200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Santa Rita</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-111.077000,24.566000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>El Cien</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-110.790000,24.400000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>San Pedro</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>-110.438000,24.048000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Loreto Mission</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Misión Nuestra Señora de Loreto Conchó, founded 1697 — the first permanent Spanish settlement in the Californias and the mother of all 27 missions of Baja and Alta California.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-111.342200,26.012300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Misión San Javier (spur)</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[1699 stone mission, 36 km up a paved-now-mostly road into the Sierra. The most beautiful surviving Jesuit mission in Baja.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-111.547800,25.849700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Puerto Escondido / Bay of Loreto NP</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Protected harbor and marine park; blue, fin, and humpback whales pass January–March. Sea-kayak launches to Isla del Carmen.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-111.327000,25.819000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Ciudad Constitución</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Agricultural service town — citrus, dates, alfalfa pumped from the fossil aquifer below. Last reliable fuel before the 150 km empty stretch south.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-111.662800,25.031200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>El Cien</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Literally 'kilometer 100' — a Pemex station and one taco stand on a long, lonely highway. Photographically iconic of remote Baja driving.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-110.790000,24.400000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>La Paz Malecón</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[5 km waterfront promenade along the Bahía de La Paz. Sunset over the bay is genuinely one of the best in Mexico. Whale-shark snorkeling Oct–Apr from local pangas.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-110.312800,24.142600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
